cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The paper specifically addresses the issue of aspect ratio variation in tracking, which is a common problem in object tracking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also proposes a novel tracking model that integrates boundary and center correlation filters, which involves machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Moreover, the paper involves optimization techniques to optimize the proposed model, which is related to mathematical optimization and numerical analysis. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.MM (Mathematical Software). 

Finally, the paper is about tracking objects in videos, which involves robotics and control. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
